This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image super-resolution, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of attention-based DenseNet and residual deconvolution also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also mentions the use of spatial attention, which is a common technique in Multimedia (cs.MM) research. Finally, the use of innovative strategies for upsampling residual information suggests that it may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category.
